history.content:
cs70 def takes up a lot of time, data 8 will be pretty easy for you, math 53 will take up a decent chunk of time, and ee16a also takes up a decent chunk of time. So I'd suggest not taking ee16a or math53 simultaneously along with cs70 (unless you're okay with putting in a LOT of time in school).

As a general rule of thumb, I never recommend taking 4 technicals, although some people can (and do) pull it off successfully (ie getting mostly As/Bs)

----

As someone who has taken CS70, EECS 47D (completion of EE16A), and Data 8 this semester, I do recommend taking Data 8 with CS70 because there is a lot of overlap in the probability portions. EE16A overlaps with those classes very late in the semester. However, this semester has been very, very painful, and I would not recommend the entire combination. I ended up PNP-ing 47D.
